{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 01 - Análisis Descriptivo Exploratorio (ADE)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Proyecto: \"¿Regular o no regular? Impacto de la regulación de IA en los ecosistemas nacionales\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**Contexto:** Chile - Boletín 16821-19 (Ley Marco de IA)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objetivos del ADE\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Comprender la estructura del dataset final\n",
    "2. Identificar patrones en regulación IA (X1) y resultados del ecosistema (Y)\n",
    "3. Detectar relaciones preliminares entre regulación y desarrollo del ecosistema IA\n",
    "4. Preparar el terreno para el modelamiento estadístico\n",
    "5. Generar visualizaciones que informen la interpretación de resultados"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup y Carga de Datos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "✓ Setup completado\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Imports\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "from scipy.stats import f_oneway, kruskal\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuración de visualizaciones\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette('viridis')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rutas\n",
    "DATA_PATH = '../data/interim/'\n",
    "OUTPUTS_PATH = './outputs/'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Crear directorio de outputs si no existe\n",
    "import os\n",
    "os.makedirs(OUTPUTS_PATH, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Setup completado\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Note: you may need to restart the kernel to use updated packages.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%pip install --quiet --upgrade pandas matplotlib seaborn scipy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Dataset cargado: 86 países × 105 variables\n",
      "\n",
      "Columnas disponibles: ['iso3', 'has_ai_law', 'regulatory_approach', 'regulatory_intensity', 'year_enacted', 'enforcement_level', 'thematic_coverage', 'regulatory_status_group', 'x1_source', 'ai_patents_per100k', 'ai_investment_usd_bn_cumulative', 'ai_investment_usd_bn_2024', 'ai_startups_cumulative', 'ai_startups_2024', 'patents_year', 'investment_year', 'startups_year', 'ai_adoption_rate', 'adoption_period', 'ai_readiness_score']...\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Cargar dataset definitivo\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(f'{DATA_PATH}sample_ready_cross_section.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset cargado: {df.shape[0]} países × {df.shape[1]} variables\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nColumnas disponibles: {list(df.columns)[:20]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Filtrar a Muestra Principal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "=== Flags de completitud ===\n",
      "complete_principal: 72 países\n",
      "complete_confounded: 72 países\n",
      "complete_extended: 62 países\n",
      "complete_digital: 69 países\n",
      "complete_regime: 72 países\n",
      "complete_legal_tradition: 72 países\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Ver flags de completitud\n",
    "print(\"=== Flags de completitud ===\")\n",
    "print(f\"complete_principal: {df['complete_principal'].sum()} países\")\n",
    "print(f\"complete_confounded: {df['complete_confounded'].sum()} países\")\n",
    "print(f\"complete_extended: {df['complete_extended'].sum()} países\")\n",
    "print(f\"complete_digital: {df['complete_digital'].sum()} países\")\n",
    "print(f\"complete_regime: {df['complete_regime'].sum()} países\")\n",
    "print(f\"complete_legal_tradition: {df['complete_legal_tradition'].sum()} países\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "✓ Análisis con 72 países (muestra PRINCIPAL)\n",
      "✓ Análisis robusto con 72 países (muestra CONFOUNDED)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Filtrar a muestra principal para análisis\n",
    "df_ade = df[df['complete_principal'] == 1].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"\\n✓ Análisis con {len(df_ade)} países (muestra PRINCIPAL)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# También preparar muestra confounded para análisis robusto\n",
    "df_confounded = df[df['complete_confounded'] == 1].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Análisis robusto con {len(df_confounded)} países (muestra CONFOUNDED)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Definir Variables Clave"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Variables definidas:\n",
      "  - Y (Resultado): 5 variables\n",
      "  - X1 (Regulación): 6 variables\n",
      "  - X2 Core (Controles): 5 variables\n",
      "  - X2 Confounders: 7 variables\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Variables Y (Resultado - Ecosistema IA)\n",
    "y_vars = [\n",
    "    'ai_readiness_score',\n",
    "    'ai_adoption_rate',\n",
    "    'ai_investment_usd_bn_cumulative',\n",
    "    'ai_startups_cumulative',\n",
    "    'ai_patents_per100k'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Variables X1 (Tratamiento - Regulación IA)\n",
    "x1_vars = [\n",
    "    'has_ai_law',\n",
    "    'regulatory_approach',\n",
    "    'regulatory_intensity',\n",
    "    'enforcement_level',\n",
    "    'thematic_coverage',\n",
    "    'regulatory_status_group'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Variables X2 (Controles)\n",
    "x2_core_vars = [\n",
    "    'gdp_per_capita_ppp',\n",
    "    'internet_penetration',\n",
    "    'gii_score',\n",
    "    'rd_expenditure',\n",
    "    'tertiary_education'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Variables X2 Confounders (post-auditoría)\n",
    "x2_confounders = [\n",
    "    'regulatory_quality',\n",
    "    'rule_of_law',\n",
    "    'has_gdpr_like_law',\n",
    "    'gdpr_similarity_level',\n",
    "    'fh_total_score',\n",
    "    'legal_origin',\n",
    "    'is_common_law'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Variables definidas:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  - Y (Resultado): {len(y_vars)} variables\")\n",
    "print(f\"  - X1 (Regulación): {len(x1_vars)} variables\")\n",
    "print(f\"  - X2 Core (Controles): {len(x2_core_vars)} variables\")\n",
    "print(f\"  - X2 Confounders: {len(x2_confounders)} variables\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
